<paragraph blockId="4.[132,681,568,1200]" pageId="4" pageNumber="187">
<emphasis box="[132,323,568,592]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="187">Comparative notes:</emphasis>
This species is known only from the macropterous form and is morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Moreira &amp; Barbosa, 2012" authorityName="Moreira &amp; Barbosa" authorityYear="2012" box="[201,616,632,656]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Paravelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lanemeloi">
<emphasis box="[201,323,632,656]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="187">P. lanemeloi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="MOREIRA, F. F. F. &amp; BARBOSA, J. F." box="[334,616,632,656]" pageId="4" pageNumber="187" pagination="58 - 68" refId="ref3361" refString="MOREIRA, F. F. F. &amp; BARBOSA, J. F. 2012. Two new species of Paravelia Breddin, 1898 and distributional notes concerning the Veliidae from Minas Gerais State, Brazil (Insecta: Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Gerromorpha). Zootaxa, 3354: 58 - 68." type="journal article" year="2012">Moreira &amp; Barbosa, 2012</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Both species have in common the coloration of the body, maculae pattern on the fore wings, and general shape of the parameres. However, 
<taxonomicName authority="Rodrigues &amp; Moreira, 2016" authorityName="Rodrigues &amp; Moreira" authorityYear="2016" box="[425,517,728,752]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Paravelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cunhai" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[425,517,728,752]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="187">P. cunhai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[525,609,728,752]" pageId="4" pageNumber="187">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[525,609,728,752]" pageId="4" pageNumber="187" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
differs from it by the length of the grasping comb on the fore tibia, which occupies 1/5 of its length, presence of a row of spines on the inner margin of the hind femur, and absence of black denticles on abdominal sterna II-VI; whereas in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Moreira &amp; Barbosa" authorityYear="2012" box="[323,443,888,912]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Paravelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lanemeloi">
<emphasis box="[323,443,888,912]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="187">P. lanemeloi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the grasping comb of the male occupies 1/3 of the inner margin of the fore tibia, the hind femur does not have spines, and abdominal sterna II-VI have small black denticles. In addition, the new species was collected in a cave from the state of Pará, northern 
<collectingCountry box="[405,467,1048,1072]" name="Brazil" pageId="4" pageNumber="187">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, whereas 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Moreira &amp; Barbosa" authorityYear="2012" box="[563,680,1048,1072]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Paravelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lanemeloi">
<emphasis box="[563,680,1048,1072]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="187">P. lanemeloi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been recorded only from the southern portion of the Espinhaço range, in the state of 
<collectingRegion box="[533,676,1112,1136]" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="4" pageNumber="187">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
, southeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[269,328,1144,1168]" name="Brazil" pageId="4" pageNumber="187">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[342,417,1144,1168]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="3.[95,174,1826,1845]" captionTargetBox="[98,1222,1034,1798]" captionTargetId="figure-94@3.[94,1228,1028,1803]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 11: Distribution records for four species of Paravelia; green square surrounded by a dotted line represents the type locality of P. cupariana, a new junior synonymy of P. spinifera." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4656560" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4656560/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="187">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
) above 
<quantity box="[499,581,1144,1168]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="187" unit="m" value="1000.0">1000 m</quantity>
elevation (
<bibRefCitation author="MOREIRA, F. F. F. &amp; BARBOSA, J. F." box="[139,409,1176,1200]" pageId="4" pageNumber="187" pagination="58 - 68" refId="ref3361" refString="MOREIRA, F. F. F. &amp; BARBOSA, J. F. 2012. Two new species of Paravelia Breddin, 1898 and distributional notes concerning the Veliidae from Minas Gerais State, Brazil (Insecta: Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Gerromorpha). Zootaxa, 3354: 58 - 68." type="journal article" year="2012">Moreira &amp; Barbosa, 2012</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="RODRIGUES, H. D. D. &amp; MOREIRA, F. F. F. &amp; NIESER, N. &amp; CHEN, P. P. &amp; MELO, A. L. &amp; DIAS-SILVA, K. &amp; GIEHL, N. F. S." box="[419,663,1176,1200]" pageId="4" pageNumber="187" pagination="1 - 47" refId="ref3650" refString="RODRIGUES, H. D. D.; MOREIRA, F. F. F.; NIESER, N.; CHEN, P. P.; MELO, A. L.; DIAS-SILVA, K. &amp; GIEHL, N. F. S. 2014 b. The genus Paravelia Breddin, 1898 (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Veliidae) in Brazil, with descriptions of eight new species. Zootaxa, 3784 (1): 1 - 47." type="journal article" year="2014">
Rodrigues 
<emphasis box="[530,585,1176,1200]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="187">et al.,</emphasis>
2014b
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
